Luis Suarez has sent a message of support to Lionel Messi and Neymar after they were booed by Paris Saint-Germain fans at the Parc des Princes on Sunday. PSG’s supporters were still clearly upset following the club’s elimination from the Champions League at the hands of Real Madrid on Wednesday evening. PSG bounced back with a 3-0 victory over Bordeaux in Ligue 1 on Sunday but supporters continuously booed, whistled and jeered Messi and Neymar. The Brazilian was even targeted by supporters when he scored PSG’s second goal of the game. After the match, Suarez hit out at PSG’s fans and paid tribute to his former Barcelona teammates. ‘As always, football has no memories,’ Suarez posted on Instagram. ‘Always with you. I love you very much.’ Mbappe getting applauded while Messi and Neymar get booed by the PSG fans lmaoooo pic.twitter.com/bAjOe6k7aw — Albi ð½ð° (@albiFCB7) March 13, 2022 Meanwhile, Cesc Fabregas also gave his support to his former Barcelona teammates. ‘Football has no memory whatsoever… it’s a shame,’ the ex-Chelsea midfielder posted on Twitter. ‘Always with you brothers.’ When asked abut the PSG supporters after the game, Mauricio Pochettino said: ‘No one likes this context, it made me sad,’ Pochettino said after the game. ‘Everyone who loves PSG is sad after the disappointment of Madrid. I’m sad with what I experienced today.’  Ukraine’s Andriy Yarmolenko in tears after scoring on return to West Ham team   Petr Cech speaks out on Thomas Tuchel’s future and sends message to new Chelsea owners   Lionel Messi and Neymar booed by Paris Saint-Germain fans after Real Madrid loss  ‘We were all affected. We understand the disappointment and the frustration. We’re all living it together, as a team. ‘We have a duty to take responsibility for what happened. We share this disappointment with the supporters.’ For more stories like this, check our sport page. Follow Metro Sport for the latest news on Facebook, Twitter and Instagram. Luis Suarez and Cesc Fabregas 